text: int fmax ( a , b ) { if ( a > b ) { return a ; } else { return b ; } } int main ( ) { int T , N , i , j , a , max , prev , cur ; scanf ( "%d" , & T ) ; while ( T -- ) { scanf ( "%d" , & N ) ; int * array ; array = ( int * ) calloc ( N , sizeof ( int ) ) ; max = 0 ; for ( i = 0 ; i < N ; i ++ ) { for ( j = 0 ; j <= i ; j ++ ) { scanf ( "%d" , & a ) ; if ( i == 0 ) { array [ j ] = a ; } else { if ( j == 0 ) { prev = array [ j ] ; array [ j ] = a + array [ j ] ; } else { cur = array [ j ] ; array [ j ] = a + fmax ( prev , cur ) ; prev = cur ; } } if ( i == N - 1 ) { if ( array [ j ] > max ) { max = array [ j ] ; } } } } printf ( "%d\n" , max ) ; } return 0 ; }
